AS PASSED SENATE
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Article 2 of Chapter 11 of Title 16 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
2 relating to offenses against public order, so as to provide for the crime of interference with
3 a first responder; to provide for penalties; to provide for definitions; to provide for related
4 matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
6 SECTION 1.
7 Article 2 of Chapter 11 of Title 16 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
8 offenses against public order, is amended by adding a new Code section to read as follows:
9 "16-11-46.
10 (a) As used in this Code section, the term:
11 (1) 'First responder' means any person or agency who provides on-site care until the
12 arrival of a duly licensed ambulance service. This shall include, but not be limited to,
13 persons who routinely respond to calls for assistance through an affiliation with law
14 enforcement agencies, fire suppression agencies, rescue agencies, and others.
