15 (2) 'Harass' means to willfully engage in any conduct directed at a first responder which
16 intentionally causes substantial emotional distress in that first responder and serves no
17 legitimate purpose.
18 (b) A person commits the offense of interference with a first responder when he or she,
19 after receiving a verbal warning not to approach from a person he or she knows or
20 reasonably should know is a first responder, who is engaged in the lawful performance of
21 a legal duty, knowingly and willfully violates such warning and approaches or remains
22 within 25 feet of the first responder with the intent to:
23 (1) Impede or interfere with the first responder's ability to perform such duty;
24 (2) Threaten the first responder with physical harm; or
25 (3) Harass the first responder.
26 (c) A person convicted pursuant to this Code section shall be guilty of a misdemeanor of
27 a high and aggravated nature."
28 SECTION 2.
29 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
